name: sfchronicle
text:
A man whose mentally ill daughter leaped to her death after walking away from an SF hospital supervisor who had let his attention lapse cannot claim damages from the city, a federal appeals court rules.

Story by @BobEgelko: https://t.co/RFMTWBaAbG

name: sfchronicle
text:
The stakes are high for this Labor Day weekend: plans to reopen businesses and schools over the next few months could be reversed if coronavirus infection rates and hospitalizations tick up.

https://t.co/AutuMISy61

name: sfchronicle
text:
A’s closer Liam Hendriks was named A.L. Reliever of the Month for July-August. 

He was 2-0 with 10 saves and a 1.10 ERA in 16 outings through August, allowing eight hits with 23 strikeouts in 16 1/3 innings. He was tied for the A.L. lead in saves.

https://t.co/oNL7TUVD2A
